snippet.title: Lego Friends Olivia's House Set Building Review Play - Kids Toys
snippet.description:
I love Lego Friends Olivia's House 3315, it's one of the first Friends set I ever bought and I desperately wanted it because it really is a build-able dollshouse! Released in 2012, this set is now retired so it's not so easy to get your hands on it, but if you can it is an awesome addition to your Heartlake CIty builds. The kitchen is chockablock full of tiny accessories - a blender, mixing bowl, teeny tiny baking pan and an enormous frying pan. And the fridge has just enough room for one carton of milk. Check out all the details in the build - I slow down the building action to take a good luck at the interesting parts. Let me know what you think of Olivia's House!

Visit Olivia’s House with all of the LEGO® Friends! Olivia, her parents and her pet cat live in a big, bright house with lots of rooms for hanging out and having fun. Help Olivia to grill up a barbecue for the girls! Mow the lawn with the lawn mower. Take Olivia’s diary out of the drawer or go swing in the yard! Then, host a sleepover or have a party! Olivia’s House is built in sections for easy rearranging. Decorate, customize and rebuild it! Includes Olivia, Mom and Dad mini-doll figures.

Includes 3 mini-doll figures: Olivia, Mom (Anna), Dad (Peter) and cat (Kitty)
Features kitchen, bathroom, bedroom, living room, barbecue, rooftop patio and outdoor table
Furniture includes a shower, toilet, sink, bed, vanity, couch, chair, coffee table, flat screen TV, refrigerator with opening door, cabinets, oven, sink, kitchen table and kitchen chairs
Accessories include diary, hairbrush, blender, salt and pepper shakers, frying pan, spatula, muffin tins, mixer, utensils, baking tray, bowl, sausage, chicken drumstick, carrots, apple, bunch of cherries and milk carton
Also includes flower accessory pack: 12 flowers, 4 ladybugs and 4 butterflies
Olivia’s House is built in sections to easily rearrange for a custom creation
Mow the lawn with the lawn mower!
Swing in the yard!
Barbecue a feast on the outdoor grill and invite the girls!
Host a party for all of the LEGO® Friends!

snippet.title: Lego Friends Heartlake Hospital Part 1 Build Review Silly Play Kids Toys
snippet.description:
A hospital! A Lego hospital for Heartlake City! There are a bazillion wonderful details in this build and I've sped up the dull bits and slowed down the interesting ones. There's a new LEGO Friends baby, a fabulous doctor, a wheelchair, a pram / stroller, a baby crib and well, too much to write about here so you'll have to watch the video. The designers have outdone themselves with all ability / disability access toilets and entrances to the hospital, a baby change table in the bathroom, a rock-able cradle, an arm and head bandage, I could go on and on and on. I think I'm going to need a couple of Heartlake Hospitals so I can do some modifications, add some wards, I have so many plans! I hope you enjoy the build, it's a fabulous one.

Part 2 https://youtu.be/VW4k_okSo4I

The LEGO® Friends Heartlake Hospital has 3 floors of medical rooms and equipment to help care for patients. There’s a nursery with crib and weighing scales, an x-ray suite with scanner and lightbox, and an examination room with a bed and microscope for checking samples. The downstairs waiting room has a reception desk and vending machine as well as an emergency entrance for those arriving by ambulance or helicopter. Includes 3 mini-doll figures plus a newborn baby figure.

Includes 3 mini-doll figures: Olivia in a nurse’s uniform, Henry and Dr. Patel, plus a newborn baby Ola figure.
Features a 3-story, modular hospital, helicopter with stretcher, ambulance with wheeled stretcher, wheelchair, stroller, medical cart and a bicycle.
Hospital features a waiting room with sliding doors, reception desk, seating area, vending machine, water cooler and an aquarium; an emergency entrance with swing doors; an x-ray suite with a revolving bed, scanner, lightbox and skeleton; a nursery with rocking crib, weighing scales and bathroom area with changing table; an examination room with bed, heart monitor and microscope; and a helipad.
Accessory elements include an arm cast, x-ray tiles, magnifying glass, sample bottles, scissors, wet floor sign and a feeding bottle.
Jump into action as the ambulance arrives and rush the patient through the emergency entrance.
Take an x-ray of Henry’s arm and put his arm in a cast to heal.
Enjoy feeding and weighing the newborn baby in the nursery.
Help the doctor treat the patients as she does her rounds with the medical cart.
Invent endless stories around caring and nurturing people back to health.
Build and rebuild this modular set in many different ways.

snippet.description:
It's time to go horse riding with Mia and Eliza! The Lego Friends Sunshine Ranch set 41039 is a cleverly designed with living apartments in the converted loft above the horse stables. This set is a big one - six bags - so I've split the massive build into two videos, here is the first!

Time for some horseback riding fun with Mia down at the Sunshine Ranch. Wake her up in the cozy apartment and make breakfast in the kitchen. Have her eat breakfast and take her downstairs to take care of the horses. This is where the fun really starts. Look after the foal and groom her, then go out riding with her friend Liza. There’s a world of great adventures waiting for these best of friends. Includes Mia and Liza mini-doll figures.

Includes Mia and Liza mini-doll figures and cute ranch animals including 2 horses, a foal, 2 bunnies, a cat and a hen
Ranch building features stables, outdoor seating area, toilet and bathroom, bedroom and a little kitchen with stove and a single bed
Also features a tree, purple bench, hen house and an area for the bunnies
Accessories include eggs, a wheelbarrow, carrots and everything needed for horse grooming
Enjoy all the great detail in this set like doors and windows that really open and close
Open the roof for easy play access
